WagerLab Privacy Policy
WagerLab Privacy Policy
Protecting your private information is our priority.
This Privacy Policy applies to WagerLab LLC
 and governs data collection and usage. For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, unless otherwise noted, all
 references to WagerLab reference WagerLab LLC its App which in turn references to the WagerLab website, WagerLab on
 the Apple App Store, and WagerLab on the Google Play Store. WagerLab is a social competition platform. By using the
 WagerLab app or website, you consent to the data practices described in this Privacy Policy.
Collection of your Personal Information
In order to better provide you with products and services offered on our App, WagerLab may collect personally
 identifiable information, such as your:
First and Last Name
E-mail Address
Phone Number
Username
If you purchase WagerLab’s products and services, we collect billing and credit card information ourselves or
 through third-party tools (ex. Apple App Store or Google Play Store in-app-purchases). This information is used to
 complete the purchase transaction.
Please keep in mind that if you directly disclose personally identifiable information or personally sensitive data
 through WagerLab’s public message boards, this information may be collected and used by others.
You may be required to provide certain personal information to us when you elect to use certain products or
 services available on the App. These may include:
registering for an account on the App
redeem a prize or award
signing up for special offers from one of WagerLab's third party partners
sending us an message via phone or email
submitting your credit card or other payment information when ordering and purchasing products and services on
 our App.
We will use your information for, but not limited to, communicating with you in relation to services and/or
 products you have requested from us. We also may gather additional personal or non-personal information in the
 future.
Use of your Personal Information
WagerLab collects and uses your personal information to operate the App and deliver the services you have
 requested.
WagerLab may also use your personally identifiable information to inform you of other products or services
 available from WagerLab and its affiliates.
Sharing Information with Third Parties
WagerLab does not sell, rent or lease its customer lists to third parties.
WagerLab may share data with trusted partners to help perform statistical analysis, send you email or postal mail,
 provide customer support, or arrange for delivery of rewards or prizes. All such third parties are prohibited from
 using your personal information except to provide these services to WagerLab, and they are required to maintain the
 confidentiality of your information.
WagerLab may disclose your personal information, without notice, if required to do so by law or in the good faith
 belief that such action is necessary for any of the following:
conform to the edicts of the law or comply with legal process served on WagerLab or the App
protect and defend the rights or property of WagerLab
act under exigent circumstances to protect the personal safety of users of WagerLab, or the public
Requesting Data/Account Deletion
You may at any time request that WagerLab delete personal information associated with your account. You can so do
 via either of the following two methods:
through the App
While logged in to the app, navigate to the settings screen
Tap on account settings
Tap on delete account
by email
Send an email to accounts [at] wagerlab [dot] app with the subject line “Account Deletion Request”
The body of the email should include your WagerLab username as well as the email address you registered with
For authentication purposes, please send this email from the email address associated with your account
Upon receipt of your data deletion request, we will deactivate your account and remove all account information from
 our databases within 30 days. We may retain certain information required to prevent fraud, track or mitigate errors,
 enforce any agreed to Terms, and/or comply with legal requirements.
Tracking User Behavior
WagerLab may keep track of the pages our users visit within WagerLab, in order to determine what WagerLab services
 are the most popular. This data is used to deliver customized content and advertising within WagerLab to customers
 whose behavior indicates that they are interested in a particular subject area.
Automatically Collected Information
Information about your computer hardware and software may be automatically collected by WagerLab. This information
 can include: your IP address, browser type, domain names, access times and referring website addresses. This
 information is used for the operation of the service, to maintain quality of the service, and to provide general
 statistics regarding use of WagerLab.
Use of Cookies
The WagerLab Site/App may use “cookies” to help you personalize your online experience. A cookie is a text file
 that is placed on your hard disk by a web page server. Cookies cannot be used to run programs or deliver viruses to
 your computer. Cookies are uniquely assigned to you, and can only be read by a web server in the domain that issued
 the cookie to you.
You have the ability to accept or decline cookies. Most Web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can
 usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer. If you choose to decline cookies, you may not
 be able to fully experience the interactive features of the WagerLab services or websites you visit.
Links
This Site/App may contain links to other sites. Please be aware that we are not responsible for the content or
 privacy practices of such other sites or apps. We encourage our users to be aware when they leave WagerLab and to
 read the privacy statements of any other site that collects personally identifiable information.
Security of your Personal Information
WagerLab secures your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. WagerLab uses technologies
 including but not limited to SSL Protocol for this purpose.
Children Under Thirteen
WagerLab does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under the age of thirteen. If
 you are under the age of thirteen, you may not use the App.
Email or Text Message Communications
From time to time, WagerLab may contact you via email or text message for the purpose of providing support,
 announcements, promotional offers, alerts, confirmations, surveys, and/or other general communication. In order to
 improve our Services, we may receive a notification when you open an email from WagerLab or click on a link therein.
 If you would like to stop receiving marketing or promotional communications via email from WagerLab, you may opt out
 of such communications by replying “STOP” or clicking “UNSUBSCRIBE” button if available.
External Data Storage Sites
We may store your data on servers provided by third party hosting vendors with whom we have contracted.
Changes to this Privacy Policy
WagerLab reserves the right to change this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you about significant
 changes in the way we treat personal information by sending a notice to the primary email address specified in your
 account, by placing a prominent notice on our site, and/or by updating any privacy information on this page. Your
 continued use of the Site/App and/or Services available through this Site/App after such modifications will
 constitute your:
acknowledgment of the modified Privacy Policy; and
agreement to abide and be bound by that Policy.
Contact Information
WagerLab welcomes your questions or comments regarding this Privacy Policy. If you believe that WagerLab has not
 adhered to this Privacy Policy, please contact WagerLab at:
